div1.p: IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES, NINTH JUDICIAL DISTRICT, DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
In the Matter of H. C. LITTOOY, On Habeas Corpus

An application having been heretofore made upon the petition of the above named H. C. Littooy for a writ of habeas corpus herein, and the said matter having come on to be heard before me on June 27, 1904, and, after hearing Messrs. Parker & Brown in behalf of said petitioner and Samuel R. Stern in opposition thereto,

It is ORDERED, ADJUDGED and DECREED that said petition be and the same hereby is denied and dismissed, and taht Edward Cudihee, sheriff of King County, Washington, to whom asid writ issued have and recover from the said petitioner, H. C. Littooy, the sum of $10.60 as costs and disbursements and that he have execution therefor.
Dated at Seattle, Washington, this 20th day of July, 1904.
Circuit Court of the United States.
In the Matter of H. C. Littooy on Habeas Corpus.
Samuel R. Stern, Attorney for Defendant.
Offices: 6304 (Sixth Floor) "The Brooklyn Annex," Spokane, Wash..
